.START 

Du Pont Co. named Nicholas Pappas, currently in charge of its polymer products businesses, to head its corporate planning department. 

The appointment, which takes effect Nov. 1, and others following from it mark the first series of high-level executive changes since Edgar S. Woolard Jr. became chairman and chief executive officer of Du Pont in April. 

Mr. Woolard said in a statement that the company's "ambitious goals for the next decade require the full attention of the executive committee," of which Mr. Pappas, as an executive vice president, is a member.
Previous planning heads haven't belonged to the executive committee, which currently comprises Du Pont's top six executives. 

Mr. Pappas, a 33-year veteran at Du Pont, will succeed James W. Giggey, who will become vice president, international, with responsibility for Latin America.
Mr. Pappas will be succeeded in his current position by Archie W. Dunham, who will become group vice president, polymer products. 

Robert v.d.
Luft, will succeed Mr. Dunham as group vice president, chemicals and pigments.
J.E. Newall, currently chief executive officer of Du Pont Canada Inc., will succeed Mr. Luft as group vice president, international. 

